MemoryEndpoints.com constraints

Purpose:
- Runtime, repository, safety, licensing, and claim-boundary constraints for MemoryEndpoints.com agents.

Last verified: 2026-07-09
Memory scope: active guardrails and policy constraints.
Public-safe status: safe for source control; contains no credential values.
Update route: update this local file for constraint changes; submit public-safe durable summaries to https://memoryendpoints.com/api/matm/memory-events/submit when authenticated.
Source of truth: user objective, repository policy docs, `.uai/totem.uai`, `SECURITY.md`, `LICENSE`, and `NOTICE`.
Next action for agents: apply these constraints before code, docs, deploy, or GitHub work.
Must not expose: raw API keys, bearer tokens, FTP credentials, database passwords, private keys, private handoff payloads, or raw one-time keys.

- Do not print or commit raw credentials.
- Do not commit E:\ftp_Deploy.txt or derived secret values.
- Runtime must remain pure Python stdlib, TypeScript, and HTML5 unless the human explicitly approves a dependency.
- Do not copy NeuralWikis public wiki surfaces or branding.
- Reuse MATM concepts and test patterns selectively; write MemoryEndpoints-specific code.
- Public claims must distinguish live, planned, gated, unsupported, and external-authority-waiting behavior.
- The license and NOTICE must preserve attribution and prohibit deceptive wholesale rebranding.
